reviews.review_text:
If you’re looking for a pure vegetarian haven in Goa, this restaurant is the place to be. From the moment you step in, you’re greeted with a pleasant ambiance that caters to both AC and non-AC seating preferences, ensuring comfort for every guest.

The Chole Bhature is an absolute standout—fluffy bhature paired with perfectly spiced chole that will leave your taste buds craving more. Equally delightful were the strawberry ice creams and shakes, which made for the perfect dessert to end the meal.

Every dish we tried was a hit, showcasing the restaurant’s consistency in flavour and quality. The service was also good, further enhancing the dining experience. Bonus points for having ample parking space, a rarity in Goa!

Overall, it’s a fantastic spot for pure veg cuisine with great food, excellent service, and a cozy ambiance. Highly recommended!

Food : 9/10
Service : 9/10
Ambience : 8/10
The food is too good and so the service is. If you're looking for Indian Veg food in Goa, this place offers large variety of it and the food is too delicious.

Very good veg food, loved the Paav Bhaaji & Pizza we ordered. Mr Jatin who served us was very friendly and had customised the recipe to suit our taste buds. Ours was the last order of the day, despite late night staff was very energetic and carried good smile
